<br>
I've been coming to this site for several months now and have enjoyed my time here.  Since the last patch, my time here has been becoming less and less enjoyable.  I do like reading the post that have information in them, comments on the game, questions and answers on quests, but even these posts are becoming more and more bleak.<br>
<br>
Why, do you ask?  One word... &quot;Taxi.&quot;  Everywhere I look, more and more people are putting that word in there sigs or posts.<br>
<br>
My friends, please, I ask you, stop it.  You are sinking yourselves to OTHER peoples level. You are sinking yourself to the level of the warrior who pesters you to port him to DL, to the rogue who wants to go to GFay.<br>
<br>
We are not taxis.  We are wizards.  If we start calling ourselves taxis, other classes will treat us more like that then we are.<br>
<br>
Graffe talked to the people at Verant.  They said there where changes but they where not going to talk about them until after E3.  Lucin is opening up in the 4th quarter (Yes, I know, I doubt it myself, but you never know.) and this is where the Combine Empire moved to when they left Norrath.  Who knows what these changes will mean.  Will they mean more ports?  Most likely.  Will they mean new spells that do more damage?  Hopefuly.<br>
<br>
I'm only lvl 28, but I am still going through what you all are going through.  People see that I am a wizard and think I can port.  I may not get as meny tells asking for it as you all do, but I still get them.  If we keep putting ourselves down by calling ourselves taxis, then that is all anyone will see when they see the name &quot;Wizard&quot;, that and nothing else.<br>
<br>
I am in a guild, the Sacred Jesters, on the Quellious server.  One of my guildmates made the mistake of calling me a &quot;soon to be taxi.&quot;  I calmly told him that if that is all he saw when he saw the name of wizard, he was mistaken.<br>
<br>
We need to stand up and be proud of our class.  Tell me, how meny other classes can do 1100 points of damage in **ONE** spell?  Or 2k for that matter?  Yes, I know the bane spells are limited, but they are there.  None that I know of.  Or if they can, not as soon as we can.<br>
<br>
Please, stop calling yourselves taxis.  Graffe, please, I'm begging you, remove the taxi overlay from the site banner.<br>
<br>
Thank you, my friends, and I'm not sorry if I got you poed.  Maybe you will start thinking like you use to and tell us how to use our spells more effectivly.<br>
<br>
Yiliamar Darkember<br>
28 Wizard of Quellious. (I want 29, dang it!  250 points of fun loving damage!! :&gt;)<br>
