The Homeless</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/useverinewolfe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Severine Wolfe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 10:21:39 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.clan-donald.com/screenshots/severine.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Begging everyone</span><hr size=1> I am proud of my class.  Always have been, always will be.  However... SHAME ON VERANT for making us what we refer to in jest.<br>
<br>
Masters of Arcane Transportation??? WTF is that?  A glorified cab driver my friend.  That's all.<br>
<br>
If I can manipulate space arcanely, how come it's only to send people away?  Why can't I manipulate space to bring someone to the group as well?  That would make me more group friendly.<br>
<br>
My evocation and alteration specialty skills are always the same because if I'm not nuking, Im shielding or porting.  That's where the rubber meets the road my friend.<br>
<br>
So unless and until Verant makes us something other than Taxis I will keep my tag the same and keep whoring ports for plat. <p>Severine <BR>
High Elf Public Transportation Professional<BR>
The meter is running and you had better pay the fare now or you're CT bound<BR>
If you choose not to decide you have still made a choice.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uoglzogl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>oglzogl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 10:23:38 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.toddpowelson.com/selfish.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Begging everyone</span><hr size=1> I agree and disaree with you. Although I think the whole taxi bit is overdone, I appreciate Graffe (a fine chap.. someone who has put more time into enhancing our class and spent a whole lot of time trying to understand its needs)standing up for what he has to say and catching VIs attention.<br>
I dont mean to be rude but I am sure you dont understand how distracting it is getting tells repeatedly from players you've never met because they need a ride somewhere. After I hit 29 I was very excited with my new TP spells (and I still like them) but by 30 I was traveling around /anon. I still take people around, but only when I choose to. I spent most of my lvl 29-30 at Ill Omen which sometimes has 110-130 people, most of whom are gonna want rides somewhere at some point. Although I am still /anon (and I dont really like having to be /anon either)... I imagine that after 34, because you can travel the world, this is a whole lot worse. I dont know, I haven't taken /anon off for a long time.<br>
My point is, it is important that VI recognises that although these spells are very nice, they dont really address any of the problems the wizard encounters throughout his career. TPs, for the most part, are for other classes and really contribute nothing to our game (sure its nice to help out friends, and even other players, but...) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 10:32:54 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Begging everyone</span><hr size=1> Actually quite a few classes can exceed 1120 in a single spell (at the same level), but the point is well taken, we aren't Wizards... and I don't go by that.  I hate Wizzy and Wizzard too, actually. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 11:26:20 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Unfortunately...</span><hr size=1> Not refering to ourselves as Taxi's will really not change anything.  Other classes refer to us as the Chauffers already anyway.  That doesn't mean I don't agree with the statement.  Its just there are certain things that are already out of our control.  I personally have had friends look at this site and commend us on having a sense of humor since we have been branded as the crybabies.  We can continue to move forward and give our opinions in forum format.  However, if we can't stop for a bit and enjoy some humor, we should just delete ourselves.  It isn't meant to be a question of concience or a great moral issue.  We deserve a bit of a break from our miserable fight.<br>
<br>
